        Our laboratory is investigating various aspects of telomere biology, with a particular focus on 
        understanding how the shortening of telomeres during replicative aging creates barriers to cell 
        proliferation and restricts the development of cancer. We use a combination of cutting-edge techniques 
        in cell biology, molecular biology, and single-cell multiomics to unravel the complex interplay between 
        telomere function, innate immune signaling, and autophagy, and how these pathways synergize to suppress 
